org.matsim.contrib.cadyts.pt

Class CadytsPtOccupancyAnalyzer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.contrib.cadyts.pt.CadytsPtOccupancyAnalyzer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PersonEntersVehicleEventHandler, PersonLeavesVehicleEventHandler, TransitDriverStartsEventHandler, CadytsPtOccupancyAnalyzerI, VehicleArrivesAtFacilityEventHandler, VehicleDepartsAtFacilityEventHandler, MatsimExtensionPoint, EventHandler

    public class CadytsPtOccupancyAnalyzer
extends Object
implements CadytsPtOccupancyAnalyzerI
    Collects occupancy data of transit-line stations

    This is probably similar to code elsewhere. However, it makes some sense to keep this here since the correct workings of cadyts (obviously) depends on the fact that the counts are actually what it thinks, and so it makes sense to decouple this from the upstream counting method and leave it here. kai, sep'13
